pyftk
=====

python binding for ftk (http://code.google.com/p/ftk/).

features
========

* use python ctypes, not c
* provides c-style interface, not oo-style

dependencies
============

python2.6
ftk 0.6

install ftk
===========

$ git clone git://github.com/htbegin/pyftk.git
$ cd pyftk
$ git checkout pyftk
$ ./autogen.sh
$ ./configure --with-backend=linux-x11:640x480 --with-fontengine=freetype \
			  --with-inputmethod=gpinyin --enable-gtk-doc-html=no --enable-opengles=no
$ make
$ make install

because the default install prefix is /usr/local, so in order to let
pyftk to find the ftk shared library, you should run one of the following
two commands before install or test pyftk:

a) export LD_LIBRARY_PATH=/usr/local/lib

or

b) sudo bash -c 'echo /usr/local/lib > /etc/ld.so.conf.d/ftk.conf' && sudo ldconfig \
		&& ldconfig -p | grep ftk

install pyftk
=============

$ git clone git://github.com/htbegin/pyftk.git
$ cd pyftk
$ git checkout pyftk
$ cd script_binding/python
$ sudo python setup.py install

test
====

$ git clone git://github.com/htbegin/pyftk.git
$ cd pyftk
$ git checkout pyftk
$ cd script_binding/python
$ ./runner.py test/

demo
====

$ git clone git://github.com/htbegin/pyftk.git
$ cd pyftk
$ git checkout pyftk
$ cd script_binding/python
$ ./runner.py demo/
